SNORT
--------

SNORT is an open-source, rule-based Network Intrusion Detection and Prevention System (NIDS/NIPS).

CAPABILITIES OF SNORT:
=======================

I. Live traffic analysis
II. Attack and probe detection
III. Packet logging
IV. Protocol analysis
V. Real-time alerting
VI. Modules & plugins
VII. Pre-processors
VIII. Cross-platform support! (Linux & Windows)

SNORT USE MODELS:

I. Sniffer Mode: Read IP packets and prompt them in the console application.
II. Packet Logger Mode:  Log all IP packets (inbound and outbound) that visit the network.
III. NIDS (Network Intrusion Detection System)  and NIPS (Network Intrusion Prevention System) Modes - Log/drop the packets that are deemed as malicious according
to the user-defined rules.




